# Example dups parameters file for CAncST pipeline.
# One row per genome. Multiple rows per genome are allowed (one per
# parameter set); the pipeline will compute and combine all of them.
#
# Format: organism k1 e1 k2 e2 w p x1 y1 x2 y2
#   organism - genome identifier (matches utils/genomes/<organism>.fasta)
#   k1, e1   - k-mer length / allowed mismatches for initial identification
#   k2, e2   - k-mer length / allowed mismatches for exclusion
#   w        - window size (bp)
#   p        - window pitch (bp)
#   x1, y1   - max-count threshold and percentage threshold for x1
#   x2, y2   - exclusion-count threshold and percentage threshold for x2
#
# Defaults below come from template/pipeline_config.yaml
# (k1=50, e1=4, k2=21, e2=2, w=300, p=50, x1=16, y1=90, x2=10, y2=10).
#
# Usage:
#   cp examples/dups_params.example template/dups_params.txt
#   # Or omit and let run_pipeline.sh auto-generate via generate_params.py.

GCF_000001215.4 50 4 21 2 300 50 16 90 10 10
GCF_016746365.2 50 4 21 2 300 50 16 90 10 10
GCF_016746395.2 50 4 21 2 300 50 16 90 10 10
